data.name: label7.Text
data.value: -The search method in which an elements to be search is checked in the entire data structure in a sequential way from starting to end is called as linear search. -Linear search is the easiest and straight most searching technique as search element is compared to all the elements in the array in sequence. The searched element is compared with first element which is positioned at index 0 then it is compared with second element in the array which is positions at index1 and so on. If searched element is matched with one of the element in the array then one can print that described element is found else desired element not exists in the array -Let Array[MAX] is integer array in which we have to search an element, Max is maximum capacity of array, is size if array or number of elements in array and item is the element to be searched. To search an element in the array, we have to travel in such a manner that each visited element would be compared to the item. If match found then print the index position and exit.

data.value: · Searching is the technique of finding an element from the given data list or set of the elements like n array, or trees. It is technique to find out an element in the sorted or unsorted list. · There are the following three cases in which an element can be found: 1. In the Best Case, the element is found during the first comparison itself. 2. In the worst case, the element is found only in the last comparison. 3. Whereas in the Average case, number of comparison should be more than comparison in the best case and less than the worst case.
